com.camerontec.catalys.core.crypto

Class EncryptionEngineBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.crypto.EncryptionEngineBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEncryptionEngine
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CryptixCrypto, NullCrypto

    public abstract class EncryptionEngineBase
extends Object
implements IEncryptionEngine
    Optional base implementation of the IEncryptionEngine interface.

    This base class simply provides protected variables for the various attributes (keys etc) required by the IEncryptionEngine interface.

    Note: Only inherit from this if it is convenient. It is not required.

      • setMyPrivateKey

        public void setMyPrivateKey(Key newMyPrivateKey)
        Description copied from interface: IEncryptionEngine
        If you will be using any methods involving private/encryption, you need to tell Crypto your private key and the other's key.

        You will encrypt the DES key that you propose with his key, so that only he can decrypt it.

        You will use your private key to sign the message, so that he, using your key to check the signature will be sure that the message came from you.

        Specified by:
        setMyPrivateKey in interface IEncryptionEngine
        Parameters:
        newMyPrivateKey - private key

        public boolean isAutoInitializeCipher()
        Description copied from interface: IEncryptionEngine

        Defaults to true.
